1
00:00:06,282 --> 00:00:09,552
-This can't be happening.

2
00:00:09,586 --> 00:00:12,155
-There isn't a ball that you
can hit that I can't return,

3
00:00:12,188 --> 00:00:14,290
young one.

4
00:00:14,324 --> 00:00:15,058
-Ha!

5
00:00:15,091 --> 00:00:16,226
Serves you right, kid.

6
00:00:16,259 --> 00:00:18,127
You're not going up
against just anyone.

7
00:00:18,161 --> 00:00:21,264
My dad was called the Golden
Retriever of Meguro

8
00:00:21,297 --> 00:00:22,665
-Did he say golden?

9
00:00:22,699 --> 00:00:23,533
-Retriever?

10
00:00:26,603 --> 00:00:29,506
[theme music]

11
00:01:44,166 --> 00:01:46,102
Your dad's
amazing, Kachiro.

12
00:01:46,135 --> 00:01:47,670
And what a life.

13
00:01:47,703 --> 00:01:49,839
Getting to work at a
great club like this.

14
00:01:49,872 --> 00:01:51,540
-Aw, come on, guys.

15
00:01:51,574 --> 00:01:52,074
It's nothing.

16
00:01:52,108 --> 00:01:53,209
He's just the coach.

17
00:01:56,245 --> 00:01:56,979
-Hey!

18
00:01:57,012 --> 00:01:58,581
Wait up for us, guys.

19
00:01:58,614 --> 00:01:59,949
Sorry we're late.

20
00:01:59,982 --> 00:02:01,484
Did you wait long?

21
00:02:01,517 --> 00:02:03,786
-Tomoka, What's that
you're carrying?

22
00:02:03,819 --> 00:02:05,221
-The lunch I made.

23
00:02:05,254 --> 00:02:06,655
-Lunch?

24
00:02:06,689 --> 00:02:08,924
-You're not gonna eat all
that by yourself, are you?

25
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:09,959
-Are you kidding?

26
00:02:09,992 --> 00:02:11,594
I brought enough for everyone.

27
00:02:11,627 --> 00:02:14,497
There's a lot of
kids in my family,

28
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:16,499
so I'm used to doing this.

29
00:02:16,499 --> 00:02:17,833
-So, Ryoma.

30
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:19,135
Practice as hard
as you can, then

31
00:02:19,168 --> 00:02:23,639
eat lots and lots of this
food I lovingly made for you!

32
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:26,942
I worked really hard for a
whole week figuring out a menu,

33
00:02:26,976 --> 00:02:28,511
and I know you're gonna like it.

34
00:02:28,511 --> 00:02:30,479
It tastes good, ask my brothers.

35
00:02:30,513 --> 00:02:32,815
-Who told them that we
were gonna come here?

36
00:02:32,848 --> 00:02:33,983
-Don't know.

37
00:02:34,016 --> 00:02:35,484
-I did.

38
00:02:35,518 --> 00:02:37,553
It's more fun with
a big group, right?

39
00:02:37,586 --> 00:02:38,554
-Ugh.

40
00:02:38,587 --> 00:02:40,055
-Momo said he'd be
joining us later.

41
00:02:40,089 --> 00:02:41,056
-What?

42
00:02:41,056 --> 00:02:43,192
Momo's coming over here as well?

43
00:02:43,225 --> 00:02:44,627
-And that's not all, either.

44
00:02:44,627 --> 00:02:46,695
-Is there anyone
you didn't invite?

45
00:02:46,729 --> 00:02:47,596
-Kachiro!

46
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:49,765
-Oh, hi, dad.

47
00:02:49,798 --> 00:02:51,167
-I'm so glad you could all come.

48
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,535
-Nice to meet you.

49
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:53,169
-Hello.

50
00:02:53,169 --> 00:02:55,037
-So, you're Ryoma?

51
00:02:55,037 --> 00:02:57,039
My son's told me all about you.

52
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:59,008
He says you're
really quite good.

53
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:00,176
-Well, uh--

54
00:03:00,176 --> 00:03:02,645
-I want you all
to have fun today.

55
00:03:02,645 --> 00:03:04,480
Follow me, and I'll
show you to the courts.

56
00:03:09,718 --> 00:03:11,153
-I see.

57
00:03:11,187 --> 00:03:12,188
How interesting.

58
00:03:12,188 --> 00:03:13,989
-Uh, uncle.

59
00:03:14,023 --> 00:03:15,257
-Huh?

60
00:03:15,491 --> 00:03:16,792
Do you want something?

61
00:03:16,825 --> 00:03:19,161
-You and those awful
magazines again.

62
00:03:19,161 --> 00:03:20,629
Here.

63
00:03:20,629 --> 00:03:22,498
Auntie wants you to get up
and take this right to Ryoma

64
00:03:22,531 --> 00:03:23,465
without delay.

65
00:03:23,499 --> 00:03:24,733
-Ah, get real.

66
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:27,570
Do I look like I'm
Ryoma's messenger boy?

67
00:03:27,603 --> 00:03:29,772
-Auntie had
another message for you.

68
00:03:29,805 --> 00:03:32,074
If you don't get this
lunch box to Ryoma by noon,

69
00:03:32,107 --> 00:03:35,177
she's going to throw out
all of your girly magazines.

70
00:03:35,177 --> 00:03:36,212
-What?

71
00:03:36,245 --> 00:03:37,179
She wouldn't!

72
00:03:37,213 --> 00:03:39,048
She couldn't do
something like that!

73
00:03:39,081 --> 00:03:40,983
She really did throw
them out the last time.

74
00:03:41,016 --> 00:03:42,785
I am so out of here!

75
00:03:45,654 --> 00:03:47,656
-You kids can
use this court.

76
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:48,824
Yes!

77
00:03:48,857 --> 00:03:51,060
It's great to be able to
play on such a cool court.

78
00:03:51,093 --> 00:03:54,163
-But please don't interfere with
any of our other guests, OK?

79
00:03:54,196 --> 00:03:55,130
Hey, Echizen.

80
00:03:55,164 --> 00:03:56,732
Teach us that kick
serve, will you?

81
00:03:56,765 --> 00:03:58,133
-No way.

82
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:59,101
-Hey, Ryoma!

83
00:03:59,134 --> 00:04:01,637
Go for it!

84
00:04:01,670 --> 00:04:02,771
-Excuse me, Coach Kato?

85
00:04:02,805 --> 00:04:03,872
-Yes?

86
00:04:03,906 --> 00:04:05,708
-I'm looking forward
to a good lesson today.

87
00:04:05,741 --> 00:04:07,643
-Certainly, Mr. Sasabe.

88
00:04:07,676 --> 00:04:09,511
Please wait for me
over by Court F.

89
00:04:09,511 --> 00:04:10,779
-What do you mean?

90
00:04:10,813 --> 00:04:12,648
Why can't we stay
here on Court A?

91
00:04:12,681 --> 00:04:13,949
There's nothing wrong with it.

92
00:04:13,983 --> 00:04:15,618
Why do we have to
walk all the way over

93
00:04:15,651 --> 00:04:17,052
to Court F for the lesson?

94
00:04:17,086 --> 00:04:18,520
We'll play right here.

95
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,189
That settles it.

96
00:04:20,189 --> 00:04:21,890
Take that back to the locker.

97
00:04:21,924 --> 00:04:23,792
See that you treat it with care.

98
00:04:23,792 --> 00:04:27,062
Don't put it on the
floor or it'll get dirty.

99
00:04:27,096 --> 00:04:28,797
-Who was that rude man?

100
00:04:28,831 --> 00:04:31,133
He's one of our
regular customers.

101
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:32,901
He's very selfish
and unpleasant.

102
00:04:32,901 --> 00:04:35,037
-We can move to
Court F if you want.

103
00:04:35,037 --> 00:04:38,207
-No, I'll just give
him a piece of my mind.

104
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:41,577
-Hey, hurry it up, will you?

105
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:42,845
-What a meanie.

106
00:04:42,878 --> 00:04:45,080
-Yeah, acts like
he's real tough.

107
00:04:45,114 --> 00:04:47,182
-I don't think I
like him very much.

108
00:04:47,216 --> 00:04:48,150
-Be right back.

109
00:04:51,186 --> 00:04:53,188
-I was sure he was
gonna tell him off.

110
00:04:53,188 --> 00:04:54,523
-I'm sorry.

111
00:04:54,523 --> 00:04:56,859
Maybe it'd be better if
we all move to Court F.

112
00:04:56,892 --> 00:04:57,893
-Don't worry about it.

113
00:04:57,926 --> 00:04:59,228
-People are like that.

114
00:04:59,461 --> 00:04:59,895
It's common.

115
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,941
-Hey, out of my way!

116
00:05:18,547 --> 00:05:19,715
-That hurt!

117
00:05:19,748 --> 00:05:22,518
Why don't you watch where
you're going, old man?

118
00:05:22,551 --> 00:05:23,052
-Give me a break.

119
00:05:23,085 --> 00:05:24,186
I'm in a hurry, kid.

120
00:05:24,219 --> 00:05:26,121
So get out of my way, OK?

121
00:05:26,155 --> 00:05:27,022
-Huh?

122
00:05:27,056 --> 00:05:29,058
After banging into me?

123
00:05:29,091 --> 00:05:29,825
No way.

124
00:05:29,858 --> 00:05:31,694
-Get out of my way!

125
00:05:31,727 --> 00:05:32,961
-Keep dreaming.

126
00:05:32,995 --> 00:05:34,163
-Look here.

127
00:05:34,196 --> 00:05:36,632
A young man like you shouldn't
be riding a bike anyway.

128
00:05:36,665 --> 00:05:38,801
You should be training
your body and your mind.

129
00:05:38,834 --> 00:05:40,135
-Listen, old man.

130
00:05:40,169 --> 00:05:41,904
You're going to regret that.

131
00:05:41,937 --> 00:05:43,639
You can't talk to me
like that and think

132
00:05:43,672 --> 00:05:46,575
you're going to
get away with it.

133
00:05:46,608 --> 00:05:47,810
Listen to what I'm saying!

134
00:05:47,843 --> 00:05:48,777
-Shut up.

135
00:05:48,811 --> 00:05:50,512
-Crazy old man.

136
00:05:50,512 --> 00:05:51,480
-Move it.

137
00:05:51,513 --> 00:05:51,955
Move it.

138
00:05:51,955 --> 00:05:52,881
Move it.

139
00:06:03,125 --> 00:06:05,794
-I can watch Ryoma play all day.

140
00:06:12,234 --> 00:06:12,801
-Echizen.

141
00:06:12,835 --> 00:06:13,502
Oh.

142
00:06:13,535 --> 00:06:14,103
Time for a break.

143
00:06:14,136 --> 00:06:14,770
Oh man.

144
00:06:14,803 --> 00:06:15,504
I can't take it.

145
00:06:15,537 --> 00:06:17,106
I'm exhausted.

146
00:06:17,139 --> 00:06:19,742
-You talk big, but
you sure lack stamina.

147
00:06:19,775 --> 00:06:21,076
-You're right?

148
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:23,045
-You're so cool, Ryoma!

149
00:06:23,045 --> 00:06:25,647
Hey, Sakuno, you're
always prompt,

150
00:06:25,647 --> 00:06:26,882
but you were really late today.

151
00:06:26,915 --> 00:06:27,516
How come?

152
00:06:27,549 --> 00:06:28,083
-Huh?

153
00:06:28,117 --> 00:06:29,952
There was no reason why.

154
00:06:29,985 --> 00:06:31,153
I was just late.

155
00:06:31,186 --> 00:06:31,787
-Hm.

156
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:33,522
Sounds fishy.

157
00:06:33,555 --> 00:06:34,656
Oh, what's in the bag?

158
00:06:34,656 --> 00:06:36,225
Let's take a look.

159
00:06:36,258 --> 00:06:37,192
I wanna see it!

160
00:06:37,226 --> 00:06:37,793
-Whoa.

161
00:06:37,826 --> 00:06:38,594
Stop it.

162
00:06:38,627 --> 00:06:39,228
Hey, don't look in there.

163
00:06:39,461 --> 00:06:39,995
-I knew it.

164
00:06:40,028 --> 00:06:40,629
Lunch for two.

165
00:06:40,662 --> 00:06:41,764
I get it.

166
00:06:41,764 --> 00:06:43,799
You were late because
you were making this.

167
00:06:43,832 --> 00:06:44,633
Who's it for?

168
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:45,868
Ryoma?

169
00:06:45,901 --> 00:06:46,568
-Oh, no.

170
00:06:46,602 --> 00:06:47,169
It's, um--

171
00:06:47,169 --> 00:06:47,970
-Come on.

172
00:06:48,003 --> 00:06:48,771
You can tell me.

173
00:06:48,771 --> 00:06:49,204
Horio?

174
00:06:49,238 --> 00:06:49,838
Kachiro?

175
00:06:49,872 --> 00:06:50,321
Katsuo?

176
00:06:53,542 --> 00:06:55,077
-Hm?

177
00:06:55,110 --> 00:06:57,179
-Hey, don't worry about it.

178
00:06:57,212 --> 00:07:02,951
This means Ryoma's fan club's
gonna grow by one more person.

179
00:07:02,985 --> 00:07:03,786
MR. SASABE: What?

180
00:07:03,786 --> 00:07:04,920
You refuse to listen to me?

181
00:07:04,953 --> 00:07:05,921
-Huh?

182
00:07:05,954 --> 00:07:06,889
What was that?

183
00:07:06,922 --> 00:07:08,590
-It was a voice.

184
00:07:08,624 --> 00:07:10,926
It came from Court
A. Let's go see.

185
00:07:10,926 --> 00:07:12,094
-That's enough.

186
00:07:12,127 --> 00:07:15,497
We can't keep
doing this all day.

187
00:07:15,497 --> 00:07:16,765
Enough of these warm ups.

188
00:07:16,765 --> 00:07:19,868
We didn't come here just so
you could watch us exercise.

189
00:07:19,902 --> 00:07:21,603
-But if you don't
warm up properly,

190
00:07:21,637 --> 00:07:24,573
it could lead to pulled muscles,
or possibly even more serious

191
00:07:24,606 --> 00:07:25,174
injuries.

192
00:07:25,174 --> 00:07:25,908
-What?

193
00:07:25,941 --> 00:07:27,576
He's gotta be kidding.

194
00:07:27,609 --> 00:07:30,078
-Look here, we're grown men,
so don't lump us together

195
00:07:30,112 --> 00:07:31,180
with those other weaklings.

196
00:07:34,616 --> 00:07:37,019
-It's Mr. Sasabe and his gang.

197
00:07:37,052 --> 00:07:38,220
-He thinks he owns the courts.

198
00:07:38,253 --> 00:07:39,788
Someone should stop him.

199
00:07:39,822 --> 00:07:42,858
-Coach Kato, I may not
look it, but I made it

200
00:07:42,891 --> 00:07:44,927
to the Inter High championships.

201
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:47,463
Consider that when you
coach me, will you?

202
00:07:47,496 --> 00:07:48,630
-Of course.

203
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:51,066
But I must warn you about
not warming up properly.

204
00:07:51,099 --> 00:07:52,067
-Oh yeah?

205
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,702
You charge us such
high tuition fees,

206
00:07:53,735 --> 00:07:55,604
but you're not gonna
teach us anything.

207
00:07:55,637 --> 00:07:57,506
Forget the boring,
small stuff, coach.

208
00:07:57,506 --> 00:07:59,174
We wanna learn how
to do dynamic things,

209
00:07:59,208 --> 00:08:00,876
like putting top
spin on the ball.

210
00:08:00,909 --> 00:08:03,145
Show us how the pros
do it, Coach Kato.

211
00:08:03,178 --> 00:08:05,914
Show us the top spin.

212
00:08:05,914 --> 00:08:08,016
-Uh--

213
00:08:08,050 --> 00:08:09,751
-That old man didn't
come here to learn.

214
00:08:09,785 --> 00:08:10,886
Listen to him.

215
00:08:10,919 --> 00:08:12,654
He's just trying to cause
trouble for Coach Kato.

216
00:08:12,688 --> 00:08:13,922
He's just a big old pest.

217
00:08:13,956 --> 00:08:16,191
-You don't know how
to do it, do you?

218
00:08:16,225 --> 00:08:18,093
I heard you didn't
turn pro because you

219
00:08:18,126 --> 00:08:20,629
had some kind of injury,
but it was probably

220
00:08:20,662 --> 00:08:24,733
because all you ever
could do was warm ups.

221
00:08:24,766 --> 00:08:26,935
-That's a terrible thing to say.

222
00:08:26,969 --> 00:08:32,007
-My son told me your son plays
on the Seigaku tennis team.

223
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:34,209
But knowing that
it's your son, he'll

224
00:08:34,243 --> 00:08:36,845
probably spend three
years chasing balls.

225
00:08:36,879 --> 00:08:38,647
It must be hard
having no talent.

226
00:08:41,083 --> 00:08:45,020
I hear they're using a
seventh grader as a regular.

227
00:08:45,053 --> 00:08:47,856
Seigaku sure has
fallen on hard times.

228
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:48,624
Ha.

229
00:08:48,657 --> 00:08:49,691
-Wait a second, Ryoma.

230
00:08:55,764 --> 00:08:58,667
-Mr. Sasabe, you can say
whatever you want about me,

231
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:01,537
but I won't allow you to
criticize my son or his school

232
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:02,638
in any way.

233
00:09:02,638 --> 00:09:04,773
Do you understand that?

234
00:09:04,773 --> 00:09:07,075
-Now, really, is that any way
to treat a paying customer?

235
00:09:09,745 --> 00:09:11,547
I guess he can't take a joke.

236
00:09:16,084 --> 00:09:17,152
-Hey, dad.

237
00:09:17,185 --> 00:09:17,853
What's up?

238
00:09:17,886 --> 00:09:19,187
What are you doing?

239
00:09:19,187 --> 00:09:20,923
-Oh, well, we're
trying to learn tennis,

240
00:09:20,923 --> 00:09:23,959
but this coach
refuses to teach us.

241
00:09:23,992 --> 00:09:27,095
-Sounds like he's being
a real pain in the beck.

242
00:09:27,129 --> 00:09:28,931
-Oh, I know him.

243
00:09:28,964 --> 00:09:29,631
-Huh?

244
00:09:29,631 --> 00:09:32,067
Are you sure?

245
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,835
-Wait a minute, Ryoma.

246
00:09:33,869 --> 00:09:35,137
-Lose the coach, dad.

247
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:38,740
With your talent, you don't
need any lessons from anybody.

248
00:09:38,774 --> 00:09:40,943
-Well, it's a sure
thing I'm a better

249
00:09:40,976 --> 00:09:42,978
player than he'll ever be.

250
00:09:43,011 --> 00:09:44,012
-Hey.

251
00:09:44,046 --> 00:09:45,614
Have you learned how
to grip a racket?

252
00:09:45,647 --> 00:09:46,982
How to grip it properly.

253
00:09:47,015 --> 00:09:50,085
Do you know how?

254
00:09:50,118 --> 00:09:51,019
-Huh?

255
00:09:51,053 --> 00:09:52,154
-Someone you know?

256
00:09:52,187 --> 00:09:54,890
-No, I've never seen
him before in my life.

257
00:09:54,923 --> 00:09:57,059
-Hey you over there.

258
00:09:57,059 --> 00:09:59,628
Do you wanna teach
me how to play?

259
00:09:59,628 --> 00:10:02,731
-You want me to teach you
the fundamentals of the game?

260
00:10:02,764 --> 00:10:05,033
-Dad, you better not
try and teach that kid.

261
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,201
-What are you saying?

262
00:10:06,234 --> 00:10:07,936
That boy can't learn
anything from that coach,

263
00:10:07,970 --> 00:10:11,173
so he's depending
on me to teach him.

264
00:10:11,173 --> 00:10:13,175
All right, I'll teach
you how to play.

265
00:10:13,175 --> 00:10:15,477
I'll show you the
beautiful techniques

266
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:18,080
that made me runner up
at the Inter High finals.

267
00:10:24,052 --> 00:10:26,555
-I don't think this
is a good thing.

268
00:10:30,525 --> 00:10:31,560
